        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 4:21PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 421 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Fickling Mill, or near
Butler, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, nickel sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Knoxville, Lee Pope, Roberta, Horns, and Fickling Mill.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
